	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p>Mail</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New Orleans</placeName> <date>May 18th</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(12)"><date>1857</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">I received your<lb/> favor of <date>28<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> Ult. addressed to me<lb/> in my official capacity.  Your numerous<lb/> friends here are rejoiced to learn of your<lb/> resumption of ministerial duties&#44; which<lb/> they regard as cause for congratulation<lb/> to yourself as well as the Israelites<lb/> of <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.  It is not in the<lb/> power of our congregation to aid you<lb/> as proposed&#8212;<hi rend="underline">it has no surplus funds</hi>.<lb/>  In order to complete the new Synagogue<lb/> &#38; buildings adjacent a mortgage had<lb/> to be given upon its <hi rend="underline">last</hi> other property<lb/> so that we are in debt with but a<lb/> limited revenue&#44; our pay<hi rend="underline">in</hi>g members<lb/> not exceeding 45.  The &#8220;Widow &#38; Orphans<lb/> Home&#8221; in which all here feel a just<lb/> pride has an insufficient revenue<lb/> and demands from <hi rend="underline">all</hi> our people</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>all the public or private surplus funds<lb/> at command.  Our city unlike <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/> has among our people few wealthy persons&#44;<lb/> and the few have such constant calls<lb/> at home&#44; that they are unable to lend<lb/> or give abroad.  With <sic>with</sic> my<lb/> warmest regards I am</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">Yours Very Respy</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Geo Jonas</persName> President</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Congregation &#8220;Dispersed of Judah&#8221;</p>
		</body>
